---
description: Prefer jCodemunch for source code, but do not force it for markdown-first work
alwaysApply: true
---

## Exploration Routing

Use `jcodemunch-mcp` for source-code exploration when symbol-aware search,
dependency analysis, or impact tracing is useful.

For markdown-first work such as notes, evidence files, and workflow docs, use
direct file reads and search first. Do not require `plan_turn` or
`jcodemunch-mcp` just to locate or read markdown files.

Use `plan_turn` only for code-focused tasks where ranked symbol or file
recommendations are likely to help.

After code edits, use `register_edit` when auto-reindexing is unavailable.
